description:
This is the brand new Busfabriken Megacenter indoor playground that just opened in Uppsala, Sweden. Wow, this indoor play center is huge!

description:
Go-Play offers three play areas, as well as an additional activity area for children to have hours of fun. Adults can relax in our Cafeteria Area enjoying free Wi-Fi, big screen TV‚Äôs and a very comprehensive menu whilst viewing their children happy at play.

The one play area accommodates from babies to 4 year olds and the second area accommodates children between the ages of 4 and 10. The Centre provides a well ventilated, safe environment for children between the ages of 0 and 10 to enjoy hours of fun. At Go-Play we are dedicated to child physical and mental improvement, and have therefore structured challenges to improve gross and fine motor skills, hand-eye coordination and spatial awareness.

The indoor Centre is fully-equipped with industry approved and hygienic child-friendly equipment including slides, soft play obstacles and mazes. At Go-Play we take safety seriously, and therefore conduct regular inspections of each piece of equipment and place trained child minders on each level at each station ‚Äì allowing parents peace of mind

The Outside area offers a track where children can enjoy hours of fun riding plastic scooters, while the parents relax enjoying a spectacular view of the Golf course and Lake

Visit our website at http://go-play.co.za

description:
Hello Friends,
I recorded this video at Arena Club Karachi also known as Arena Recreational & Sports Complex. Arena Club is located at Karsaz Karachi next to Bahria Maritime Museum Karachi people also called Navy Maritime Museum Park Karachi. 

Just to inform you that I have already uploaded detailed videos on Navy Maritime Museum Karsaz Karachi and a very good video on PAF Museum Karachi also known as PAF Museum Park here is the link of both videos for your consideration.

Maritime Museum Karachi 2020
https://youtu.be/WQ15IJb3uDo
PAF Museum Karachi 2020
https://youtu.be/s6ysHisYvnM

Now back to this video, Arena Club offers membership on yearly basis and if don't have Arena Club membership so you can get entry by purchasing ticket. The Arena Club Ticket Price 2020 is Rs. 875/- per person and children's under 3.6 feet height are free to enter inside.It has a good buffet restaurant called Arena Rangoli where you can taste variety of tasty and spicy dishes.

Arena sports club has lots of indoor games & video games for kids as well as adults. In my opinion this is the best place for physical activities for kids. You can enjoy Bowling, 8 Ball Pool, video games, 3d Virtual Video Games also it has very good ice skating area also they arrange ice skating camp for training. It has a very good Arsenal Gaming area like Chunky Money, Dolmen Mall Fun Land and like Sindbad further there is a very good video game machine where you can play car racing games like parking frenzy 2.0 3d game and other car race games.

I think this place is best for top extreme sports activities minded now a days physical activities for kids are very important. In Short it has best games under one specially Turbo Driving Car Racing Games.

Youtube: https://www.youtube.com/farhanjafri

description:
"Daniel Gets Mad"
Daniel Tiger and Prince Wednesday are very excited to play at the beach today. But then it rains, and Mom Tiger says they cannot play outside, making them very mad. Mom Tiger helps the boys deal with their mad feelings. Once they are calm, they can think clearly. They have a grr-ific plan to make an INSIDE beach! 

"Katerina Gets Mad"
It's New Instrument Day at Music Man Stan's Music Shop. Everyone is excited, but Katerina Kittycat gets mad when someone else picks the instrument she wants to play. Music Man Stan helps guide Katerina through her mad feelings. He teaches everyone how to dance, stomp and sing their mad feelings away. This episode deals with mad feelings and offers the strategy- When you feel so mad that you want to ROAR...take a deep breath and count to four. 1...2...3...4...

description:
enjoy a fun Best Day Ever with the boys!!

JOIN OUR FAM!! --- http://goo.gl/rfgp8V

Best Date Day Ever 1074

Today is a super special day!! A few days ago, I took Adley on a fun daddy daughter date, and everyone has been commenting and sending me DMs saying that I need to take Niko out for a fun day date!! So we get ready for the day and head out, not knowing where exactly we are going to end up. It's a mystery!!

We end up at the mall, because it's got all the things my daredevil 1.5 year old boy would like: Play park, candy shops, and toy stores. Our first stop is getting Niko a new toy, and the things Niko wants more than anything are ball pit balls!! lol 

After getting those gifts, we head down to the indoor park in the mall to play on the slides and tubes. We play with some of the balls racing down the slides, we then head over to the arcade where Niko rides a motorcycle and play new games. 

Heading back home, we surprise Adley by picking her up from school. We head home, telling Jenny all the cool things Niko and I did and Adley tells us about her fun day at school.

I head to the Spacestation to get some work done and when i get back home, the whole family is playing hide n seek from me. After finding everything, Jenny and Adley show me a new trick they've been practicing and Adley  sets up and indoor obstacle course!!

description:

and YOUR MERCH IS BACK!!   http://aforadley.com/

JOIN OUR FAM!! --- http://goo.gl/rfgp8V

Best Daredevil Day Ever 1155

One of the families favorite things about October is all of the Halloween decorations. Jenny, Adley and Niko Bear found some awesome bats that go perfect for the holiday and decide to hang them on the door. Adley, being the loving little girl that she is, groups them in families and names them after all of us. 

Once the door is all decorated, the find me downstairs so they can show me the great job that they did. After decorations, Adley comes up with a brand new game called statue! the rules are easy, Adley and Niko are statues, Jenny sells them, and I buy them. But they are crazy. The Adley statue moves around when I'm not looking while the Niko Bear statue has a button to make it come a live and run around the room. haha I love pretend play with the kiddos!!

With the new game done, I have to show you guys a new trick that the kiddos and I learned. We can hang from the ceiling in the kitchen!! It's hilarious, though Jenny wishes we didn't use the house like a park toy. We then head to the backyard splash pad to find some rocks for arts and crafts time.

We love doing little DIY creative projects with the kiddos, but these are extra special, because we are going to take these rocks to the construction site of a brand new LDS Temple. These temples are super important to us, so its awesome that we get to put little memories into the foundation. Adley draws pretty flowers, Niko colors his rock so good, and Jenny makes a cute rock for her and baby Navey and I make a rock about our family and how much we love each other. ( Also with a little pirate theme for pirate island lol)

After dropping of the rocks and doing some work at the lake lot, I'm home for the night! I also brought gifts for the whole family. We have A for Adley shirts again!! We have a brand new company making them and they look so good. The colors are bright, the images look great, and we are excited to share them with you guys again!! Prices are still the same, we want them to be easy for you to get. If you bought a shirt before and there were problems with it, we want to help. After unboxing the surprise, it's time to start our bed time routine and end this amazing Best Day Ever!!

description:
This video shares 16 at home activities you can do with your toddler. I‚Äôve been working on this video for too long. But, with many people stuck at home, I hustled to finally get it done! I originally started this post with 1-year-olds in mind. That‚Äôs how old my little guy is. But, many of these will work for 2 and even 3-year-olds as well.

#momvlog #toddler

See 13 more learning activities for toddlers: https://youtu.be/qXW7oNtA0Pc

Read the post for more info: https://www.butfirstcoffeeblog.com/16-activities-to-do-at-home-with-your-young-toddler/
Read my review on Lovevery Play Sets: https://www.butfirstcoffeeblog.com/lovevery-play-kits-review/
Get the Lovevery Play Kit Subscriptions: https://www.butfirstcoffeeblog.com/recommends/lovevery-play-kits/

Tips for Playing with 1-Year-Olds
Model the Activity: Very often you‚Äôll need to model an activity for a toddler. We can‚Äôt always just put it in front of them an expect they know what to do. Show your child the way to play with it and then offer it back.
Parallel Play ‚Äì Parallel play can often help extend the length of time your little one plays. Parallel play is when you see two kids playing next to each other but not actually with each other. You can mimic that same thing by ‚Äúplaying‚Äù to encourage them to continue playing with whatever toy they have.
At their level tables and shelves ‚Äì It‚Äôs super helpful to make your space accessible for your little one. Having toy shelves that are right at their level is ideal. It‚Äôs also great if you have a toddler-height table for them to use. It‚Äôs a little more expensive, but I also really love using a learning tower, which allows kids to stand at counter-height in the kitchen to play and do activities.

Best  Day Ever 1003

Nobody's home!! Jenny went to breakfast with her sister and took Niko Bear with here, so Adley and I are home alone and can do whatever we want and be a load as we want!! Now that we don't need to follow our normal routine, we head upstairs to jump on the bed!! That's fun, but we want to have more fun. So we think of what we can do. Adley has the great idea of going to Rush! It's one of her favorite places because they have games and bounce houses and inflatable horses!

But guess what, they also have something that Aldey has never done before, roller skating! We decide that now that she's a 4 year old that she can try it for the first time! We get some skates. We get he cutest little skates and put them on Adley. We then have to walk to the indoor skate park and its a struggle muffin! Adley is all over the place, slipping around and doing the splits. I help her over to the rink where we skate around for a while! It's so fun watching her learn new things!!

After we've had fun roller skating, we head over to the bounce houses where Adley does all sorts of tricks. I'm in there too, till they kick me out for not being a kid lol! We then head over to the drift carts so Adley can go for a ride and, another first, we try out the ginormous bumper cars. Adley loves them!! We then end our daddy daughter family fun date with Ice cream!

Before this best day is over, I need pack. I'm a fan of traveling, even though it takes me away from the family, it does give me the opportunity to do something that I really enjoy but don't get a chance to do often, and that's listen to audiobooks! I love learning from other's experiences and trying to improve myself as a person, and Audible has a great selection of books that can help me out. And because of our great friendship with Audible, they sponsored part of this video and I was able to hook you guys up. Follow the link up top and you can get all that free stuff!! go show them so love, they are awesome! Ok I'm out of here, have the best day ever!!

title: How to Play Dodgeball
tags: playing,sports,games,dodgeball,dodge,ball,rules,strategy,winning,activities,kids,children
description:
Full Playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLLALQuK1NDrh8U61-0VzfUFk67mCtogg6
-
-
Like these Kid's Activities !!! Check out the official app http://apple.co/1ThDIrx

Watch more Games for Kids videos: http://www.howcast.com/videos/284392-How-to-Play-Dodgeball

Dodgeball is a great game to play for exercise and fun with minimal equipment, and here is how it's done.

Step 1: Set up the court
Designate a centerline on the court and line the balls along the centerline before the start of the game. Courts should be around 50 feet long and 30 feet wide with walls or fences at either end. 

Tip
Basketball courts work well for dodgeball. 

Step 2: Start the game
Position an equal number of players at either end of the court. Recruit someone to blow a whistle to indicate the start of the game.

Step 3: Get balls
Rush to the centerline to grab as many balls as you can at the start signal.

Step 4: Throw and catch the ball
Throw balls at players to get them out. If you catch a ball thrown by an opposing player, the thrower is out and a player on your team who has been eliminated can reenter play.

Tip
You can use a ball in your hands to block balls coming at you, but if you drop the ball you're out.

Step 5: Ending the game
End the game when all players from either team have been eliminated.

Did You Know?
The longest dodgeball marathon lasted for 24 hours and two minutes, performed by the New York Epic professional team.

description:
a Best Day Ever at Universal Amusement Park with friends!

JOIN OUR FAM!! --- http://goo.gl/rfgp8V

Best Donut Day Ever 1036

Welcome to the first official day of our family vacation to California!! Not travel, no routines, just us having as much fun as we possibly can! While everyone is getting ready to head out, Adley and I give you a quick tour of our hotel! Niko Bear is spoiled with his own room cause Adley decided that she needs to share a room with me and Jenny!!

We load up into our ginormous van and head back to Universal studios! Because of travel, we only got to do the Harry Potter world, so today we are going to have fun in the rest of the park!! Right when we walk in we see some of Adley's favorite characters, Princess Fiona and Shrek!! Adley gets some high fives before we head down to the dinosaur area! The kids have tons of fun running round and exploring, while Jenny and I go on the Jurassic World ride!! (Adley was just a little too short to come with us, but next time!!)

While Jenny and the rest of the crew go on more rides, Issac and I do our best Mr. Mom routines and keep an eye on the kiddos while we also look for a churro for Adley.

Next up, we head to an animal actors show and the kiddos love it! Dogs, cats, farm animals, birds!! tons of animals doing tricks and being awesome!! it was tons of fun!! It's almost time to head back to the hotel, but first we get the kiddos the worlds biggest donut! (maybe not the worlds, but its HUGE!!)

Back at the hotel, we get ready to go swim and float in amazing swimming pools. But first, some Hide N Seek!!

The family goes to Universal Studios for the very first time!

JOIN OUR FAM!! --- http://goo.gl/rfgp8V

Best Harry Potter Day Ever 1035

7 am is really early in the morning! But it makes it all better when your up this early to go on another surprise vacation! We wake up the kiddos and get them all ready before jumping in the purple Tesla to head to the airport. We meet some friends there (mystery guests you could say) and get all settled on the airplane. 

A short time later we are in sunny and warm California!! We head to the car to go to the first big surprise and on the walk, we discover a brand new way to carry Niko Bear around hahaha. First stop, Universal Studios! This is Adley very first time here, so she‚Äôs taking it all in. She meets up with some animals like Curious George and can‚Äôt wait to give him a hug!! We then head to one of Jenny‚Äôs most favorite place, probably second after Hawaii, Harry Potter world. We get look at wands, get candy from Honeyduke‚Äôs, and then we jump on a ride! They won‚Äôt let me film even though I tried, but I got caught!

We get butter beers to try and they are soooo good. Niko isn‚Äôt sure what to think at first, but then he realizes he loves it and doesn‚Äôt want to share with anyone anymore!!

After having tons of fun at Harry Potter, we go to the rest of Universal, where we see the dinosaur park area with a playground and a brand new playground for Adley to play on. Baby brother would be playing too if he wasn‚Äôt fast asleep! We play as long as we can till we‚Äôre all tired from getting up early and having a great day! We head to the hotel to get some shut eye so we can have another family fun Best Day Ever tomorrow!!

description:
Adley and Niko have the BEST NIGHT EVER at our new favorite place!!

JOIN OUR FAM!! --- http://goo.gl/rfgp8V

Best Ball Pit Day Ever 1015

We were not ready for this!! I got home from the spacestation and Jenny said she found this new place not far from us that was a brand new indoor park. It sounded really fun and it would be some great family fun. But this place was even better than we thought. As soon as we got there, Adley was wanting to run and play, she could hardly contain her excitement (and honestly, I felt the same way)!

We climbed all over his super fun playground toy, with slides and balance bridges, we found trampolines that we did tricks on and one that you could jump on a huge air blob you could jump on. The was a balance beam over a foam pit that Adley and I did tricks on and we found the ultimate ball pit, and it was Niko's first time in one. At first he didn't really seem to understand, but then he started having tons of fun. So cute watching the kids just run all over the place, with some many fun things to do. Adley is a little daredevil, she has no fear! They have an obstacle course machine on some trampolines and Adley does amazing at it!!

They also have a sky coaster track that Jenny and I took turns riding on. Adley was just a little to short to ride, but she had fun watching her mom and dad zip around the ceiling. We had so much fun and as we were getting ready to leave, we found even more things for us to do. We're definitely going to come back! 

Everyone really needs to check this place out. This isn't a brand deal or a partnership, me and my family genuinely had so much fun that I wanted to give them a shout out and thank them for the amazing time!!

Urban Air Trampoline and Adventure Park -- http://www.urbanairtrampolinepark.com/locations/Utah/Clearfield

When we get home the kids are literally exhausted and go straight to bed (maybe a new bed time routine lol). So Jenny and I eat some dinner and have a little catch up session with you guys cause it's been a while since we had a real talk and we've missed you guys!

description:
David and his brothers had a family fun playtime with indoor Playground Play Area for Kids! This Play Area for children had giant slides, kids can slide, jump, climb on the playground. There's even a toddler play center with toys and ball pits. There's also plasma cars racing kids can ride. Great video for Kids who loves to have fun playing. Subscribe for more Family fun time:https://goo.gl/SDhNuj

The boys get to burn off some excess energy in this video taken at Zippy Zoom Indoor Playground in Welland, Ontario. http://zippyzoomplayground.com/

The facility is 8000 sq ft and includes several slides,  tons of plasma cars, a ball pit, ball blasters, a ball fountain machine, a spinner seat, a waterbed/trampoline and fully padded floors.  The facility is well built with all the kids safety in mind.  Even the parents can follow the little ones into the playground and get a workout themselves.  We've seen adults try and enjoy the plasma cars in the facility as well!

Their prices are very reasonable and if the kiddies enjoy themselves a lot, then we suggest getting a monthly membership or even a yearly.  This is a sure cure for those winter blues when outdoor playground activities are not possible due to weather.  Zippy Zoom also has a small snack bar for snacks and drinks but if that is not enough, they also allow Domino's pizza to deliver.  The facility has enough space for seating while dining and reading as well if that is your preference.  Most importantly, the facility has washrooms onsite for those emergencies that all families with small kids know!

Overall, the trip to Zippy Zoom in Welland, Ontario is well worth the drive!  The kids get to burn off their energy (they slept very well that night!), Dad get to follow along and get some exercise as well and everybody had fun no matter what the weather is outside!  

Check them out and you might see us there because we are planning on making another visit!

tags: Amy Sturkey,pediatric,physiotherapy,developmental delay,low tone,gross motor,#pediPT,#pedsPT,#specialneeds,hypotonia,paediatric,PT,OT,physical therapy,#sn,telehealth,home program,Down syndrome,Autism,Cerebral Palsy,How to help my child,4 year,5 year,6 year,7 year,8 year,9 year,10 year,11 year,12 year,child,kid,occupational therapy,#pedsOT,#pediOT,ball handling,eye hand coordination,#autism,easy,progression,tennis ball,small ball,2 hand catch,trap
description:
My name is Amy Sturkey. I am a pediatric physical therapist. On this playlist, I teach ball-handling skills. I have amazing helpers of different ages to help teach these skills.  I start with simple catching skills appropriate for a 4 to 5-year old. Through the playlist, the skills will become challenging enough to be tricky for a 16 to 18-year-old. I explain how I teach these skills as a pediatric therapist with a diverse clientele.  I'd like to thank three families for allowing me to share their children. I'd like to thank these kids, Kai, Marcus,  D'Mitri, Louisa, and Ariel for being willing to help.

 I hope you find these ideas useful and simple. My website is www.pediatricPTexercises.com  My Facebook page is Pediatric Physical Therapy Exercises. My Instagram is PediatricPTexercises. My Pinterest is amysturkey/pediatric-physical-therapy/. My informational books, "A is for Autism",  "C is for Cerebral Palsy", and  "D is for Down Syndrome" are available on Amazon.  "A is for ADHD" should be released soon.  "Pediatric Physical Therapy Strengthening Exercises for the Hips" and "Pediatric Physical Therapy Strengthening Exercises for the Knees" are also now available. Do not hesitate to contact me at amysturkey@gmail.com with questions, concerns, or favorable reviews! Please note: I am sorry, but I am unable to provide treatment recommendations for a child I have not personally evaluated.
I am so honored to have people from all over the world watch my videos. I have reviewed and corrected the closed captions for this video so that you might understand what I am saying even if you don't speak English. I hope the directions below are helpful to you. 
To turn on Captions, click CC in the bottom right corner of the video
To choose a different caption language:
At the bottom right, click Settings. It looks like a wheel.
Click Subtitles/CC.
Select a language.
If the language isn't listed when you click Subtitles/CC:
Click Auto-translate.
Select a language.
Of course, if the captions are in the way of viewing the details in the video, you can always turn them off in the bottom right-hand corner of your video screen.

title: Why safe playgrounds aren't great for kids
tags: playground,by design,Vox.com,vox,explain,explainer,christophe haubursin,playground design,by design vox,vox by design,by design playgrounds,vox playgrounds,playgrounds vox,playgrounds by design,childhood studies,public spaces,public space design,urban planning,urbanism,sociology,childhood development,children playgrounds,children's playgrounds
description:
There's a case for making playgrounds riskier.

This video is presented by Wix, sign up at https://www.wix.com/go/vox

Subscribe to our channel! http://goo.gl/0bsAjO

The stereotypical modern playground ‚Äî with its bright colors and rubberized flooring ‚Äî is designed to be clean, safe, and lawsuit-proof. But that isn't necessarily the best design for kids.

US playground designers spent decades figuring out how to minimize risk: reducing heights, softening surfaces, and limiting loose parts. But now, some are experimenting with creating risk. A growing body of research has found that risky outdoor play is a key part of children‚Äôs health, promoting social interactions, creativity, problem-solving, and resilience. 

Some communities are even experimenting with ‚Äúadventure playgrounds,‚Äù a format with origins in World War II Denmark, where bomb sites became impromptu playgrounds. Filled with props like nails, hammers, saws, paint, tires, and wood planks, these spaces look more like junkyards than play spaces ‚Äî and parents are often kept outside of the playground while children are chaperoned by staff. Now, that question of keeping children safe versus keeping children engaged is at the heart of a big debate in playground design.

Our Playroom Tour - 3 Play Zones Every Kid Needs

The Parenting Junkie will walk you through how to design a play space. You‚Äôll get a playroom tour, more specifically a minimalist playroom tour.  Throughout the minimalist inspired playroom tour you‚Äôll see the 3 play zones kids need, including the messy zone, quiet zone, and play zone.  You‚Äôll see minimalist play space and minimalist inspired playspace. The minimalist playroom illustrates how kids are more likely to engage in independent play when there isn‚Äôt clutter from all the toys. Another way to describe this type of playspace is a simplicity play space or simplicity playroom.  The messy zone includes the kids art room or kids craft room.  It‚Äôs also set up in a way that it can serve as a  toddler art room or toddler craft room. The playroom tour shows ways to store tiny toys so that it is safe to use as a toddler playroom and toddler play space as well.  With the playspace being minimalist inspired, the minimalist toddler play space and minimalist toddler playroom show how toddlers too can engage in independent play.  Play space design is an important aspect of designing any playroom, playspace, and play area for kids.  It should have natural light where possible as well.  In the quiet zone you can create a cozy space for kids. A nice quiet space for kids where they are able to wind down and read or relax. This can also serve as your cozy space for toddlers.

description:
YouTube Kids Keith and Bree play Watermelon Smash Game Meme at the swimming pool with water and slime?  Will they get slime or water on their head?
Watermelon Smash is available exclusively at Target.
This is the perfect summer outdoor game with friends and family.
You can also use the plastic seeds for indoor play.

Watermelon Smash was provided free by Yulu toys for review.

#watermelonsmash #yulutoys 

Take a chance on the Watermelon Smash game but don‚Äôt be the one to get splashed. This all new hilarious twist on the water roulette game challenges each player to press the watermelon against your head as many times as said on the spinner. A suspenseful game in which you never know when the watermelon will fully crack open. If it cracks on your turn, you either get covered with water or plastic watermelon seeds and you are out of the game.

Be the last player left to avoid having the watermelon crack open and you win. Great for indoor play with seeds or outdoor play with water.

title: 2020 Montgomery County Sports Hall of Fame Induction Ceremony
tags: montgomery county,maryland,sports,hall of fame,induction,ceremony,Tom Brown,Johnny Holliday,Jeri Ingram,Roy Lester,Curtis Pride,Amy Wood
description:
Hello and welcome to the Montgomery County Sports Hall of Fame 2nd Annual Induction Ceremony

Curtis Pride (Baseball), Johnny Holliday (Broadcasting), Amy Wood (Field Hockey), Jeri Ingram (Tennis), Tom Brown (Baseball and Football) and the late Roy Lester (HS Football Coach) are all stellar in their history of representing our community and in their commitments to make Montgomery County a better place.

Curtis Pride's story--born severely hearing impaired, yet excelled in three sports--will bring tears to your eyes. Tom Brown played in the pros in two sports; baseball for the Senators and won three NFL title rings with the Green Bay Packers. Jeri Ingram still holds records in Montgomery County and the University of Maryland. Coaches, like Amy Wood and Roy Lester, are often the unsung heroes behind the stars. But they not only build athletes, they build young men and women who are our county's future. And Johnny Holliday! He is much, much more than the voice of the Terps. Humble and generous of spirit.

Olympic Gold Medalist and 2019 Inductee Dominique Dawes delivers a special message after landing a surprise opening.

Thank you for joining us!

Please visit our website to learn more about this year's inductees, past inductees, and how you can help support the Montgomery County Sports Hall of Fame https://mcshf.org

description:
Halloween crafts and painting with the kids üéÉ

JOIN OUR FAM!! --- http://goo.gl/rfgp8V

Best Doctor Day Ever 1154

Breakfast is the most important meal of the day. So when I decide to make pancakes, I use only the best ingredients...Aldey and Niko Bear!! This morning starts off with some dad vs kids running around the house, the kiddos trying to get away from me as use them to make pancakes. I crack Niko like an egg, pour flour from Adley, and cook both Adley and Niko shaped pancakes on the grill, which is actually a couch, but its good old family fun.

Once morning play time is over, we load up the purple tesla and head off to the doctor. Navey needs a check up to make sure she is still doing great without extra oxygen and Adley and Niko need to get shots. They are so brave. They didn't even cry!! After all the test and shots, it's off the beach of pirate island for a family picnic. While eating, we find that the fish in the lake are very interest in our chicken nuggets. Adley drops a piece in and it's quickly snatched up. I hold a piece just outside the water and the fish jumped up to get it from me. Jenny tries a science experiment and puts her shoe near the water. Sure enough, the fish thought it was food and go for it.

After lunch, it's time to play pirates and fairies with the kiddos. Fairy Adley has some flying dust that pirate dad and pirate Niko are tying to get. After tons of fun and running around at the lake, we head home for some arts and crafts, halloween gifts for the kiddos to unbox, and playing with new toys in the ultimate game room.

Learn how to make a Pikler Triangle! This was a really fun DIY project for kids that you can do yourself with some basic woodworking tools and some easy-to-find materials. We love rock climbing, so when a project came along where we could start to get our son interested, we jumped on it!

We'd love to hear your feedback!

The Pikler Triangle was developed by a Hungarian Pediatrician named Emmi Pikler many years ago and parents have been using it ever since to help kids improve gross motor skills, confidence, and teach them awesome skills. We love it, and if you're interested in building something for your kids, they're going to love this too.

If you make one of these Pikler Triangles please send us some pictures! We'd love to check it out!

title: Virtual Behind the Scenes at Romano Gymnasium
description:
Join former UMD Bulldog Basketball Head Coaches and current athletic administrators, Karen Stromme and Gary Holquist in a Virtual Bulldogs Behind the Scenes tour of Romano Gymnasium exploring recent renovations including historical perspectives.

Romano Gymnasium has been the home of Bulldog Men‚Äôs and Women‚Äôs Basketball and Volleyball for over a half-century. The historic facility opened December 12, 1953 and underwent a renovation in 1986 as well as a significant remodel throughout 2019-2020. Romano Gymnasium is the largest indoor gathering space on the UMD campus and one of the larger venues in Northern Minnesota. The space is a highly visible area of campus that is seen by all students, University employees, and community. It is often looked at as the ‚Äúfront porch‚Äù of the institution. Romano Gymnasium is much more than an athletic team space, event space, and teaching space - it is a community space.

*This event was recorded via Zoom on October, 20 2020.*

Bulldogs Behind the Scenes is a UMD alumni event that gives you an inside look at local industry leaders. Alumni and friends will enjoy facility tours, access to company leadership, and connecting with each other through curiosity and learning.

Learn more about our virtual programs at d.umn.edu/alumni

You can learn more about Romano by visiting https://umdbulldogs.com/sports/2013/8/30/RomanoGym.aspx

description:
The theme of this video is "to explore." Taika and Saima visit a big indoor playground.  The playground is loaded with exciting tunnels and passageways which allows for a lot of exploration. In the video, you'll see Taika and Saima playing in a ball pit, climbing different play structures, squeezing through tunnels, jumping on trampolines, driving toy cars, and running and exploring everything they could see.

The video is educational; it's a video designed to introduce toddlers to spelling. Although they may not be able to spell the words yet on their own, the video serves to introduce them to the wonderful world of letters and words. The words spelled are explore, slide, ball, car, climb and tunnel.
